value.value: A central Y-shaped metacarpal is the result of a partial fusion of two central metacarpals (i.e., metacarpals 2-4) of the hand, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Central Y-shaped metacarpals may be seen as a result of a central polydactyly with partial fusion of the duplicated metacarpal.

Swan neck-like deformities of the fingers

value.value: A swan neck deformity describes a finger with a hyperextended PIP joint and a flexed DIP joint. The most common cause for a swan neck-like deformity is a disruption of the end of the extensor tendon. Conditions that loosen the PIP joint and allow it to hyperextend, for example conditions that weaken the volar plate, can produce a swan neck deformity of the finger. One example is rheumatoid arthritis. Another cause are conditions that tighten up the small (intrinsic) muscles of the hand and fingers, for example hand trauma or nerve disorders, such as cerebral palsy, Parkinson's disease, or stroke.

Bir kuğu boynu deformitesi, aşırı genişlemiş PIP eklemi ve esnemiş DIP eklemi olan bir parmağı tanımlar. Bir kuğu boynu benzeri deformite için en yaygın neden ekstansör tendonun ucunun bozulmasıdır. PIP eklemini gevşeten ve aşırı genişlemesine izin veren koşullar, örneğin volar plakayı zayıflatan koşullar, parmakta bir kuğu boynu deformitesi oluşturabilir. Bir örnek romatoid artrittir. Başka bir neden, el ve parmakların küçük (intrinsik) kaslarını sıkıştıran koşullardır, örneğin el travması veya serebral falsi, Parkinson hastalığı veya inme gibi sinir bozuklukları

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: A swan neck deformity describes a finger with a hyperextended PIP joint and a flexed DIP joint. The most common cause for a swan neck-like deformity is a disruption of the end of the extensor tendon. Conditions that loosen the PIP joint and allow it to hyperextend, for example conditions that weaken the volar plate, can produce a swan neck deformity of the finger. One example is rheumatoid arthritis. Another cause are conditions that tighten up the small (intrinsic) muscles of the hand and fingers, for example hand trauma or nerve disorders, such as cerebral palsy, Parkinson's disease, or stroke.

value.value: Deformita labutí šíje popisuje prst na ruce s hyperextentovaným PIP kloubem a flexovaným DIP kloubem. Nejčastější příčinou je narušení konce šlachy extenzoru. Stavy, které uvolňují PIP kloub a umožňují mu hyperextendovat, například stavy, které oslabují volární ploténku, mohou způsobit deformitu labutí šíje prstu. Jedním z příkladů je revmatoidní artritida. Další příčinou jsou stavy, které napínají malé (vnitřní) svaly ruky a prstů, například trauma ruky nebo nervové poruchy, jako je mozková obrna, Parkinsonova choroba nebo mrtvice.
